This should be a question for ONNX library. Are you using an ARM machine? There is no pre-build ARM distribution for ONNX 1.8.0. Still, you should be able to build it from source. Do you encounter any error while installing ONNX 1.8.0 from source distribution?

Please follow the steps here: https://github.com/onnx/onnx#build-onnx-from-source Thanks!

@jcwchen  , I followed the below steps for installing the ONNX 1.8.0 from the source. 

I used the source file from the below link. 
https://github.com/onnx/onnx/releases


```
export CMAKE_ARGS="-DONNX_USE_PROTOBUF_SHARED_LIBS=ON"
git clone --recursive https://github.com/onnx/onnx.git
cd onnx
# prefer lite proto
set CMAKE_ARGS=-DONNX_USE_LITE_PROTO=ON
pip install -e 
```
